Zabiele  is a village in the administrative district of Gmina Wielbark, within Szczytno County, Warmian-Masurian Voivodeship, in northern Poland. It lies approximately  north-east of Wielbark,  south of Szczytno, and  south-east of the regional capital Olsztyn.
